
                                            Police say at least three people were shot in the area on Saturday.
                                         Editor's note: Police told Eyewitness News that the shootings took place in Marikana informal settlement. Western Cape police spokesperson Lieutenant-Colonel Andre Traut has now clarified that it took place in Hanover Park. CAPE TOWN - Two people have been killed and one wounded in shooting incidents in Hanover Park on Saturday afternoon. Three police constables were also wounded in the attack.  They are currently receiving treatment in hospital. The police's André Traut told EWN that the shootings took place on Saturday afternoon around 5:30pm. Traut says they’re investigating. “Yesterday at about 17:30 police members reacted to shooting incidents which occurred in the Hanover Park area when they came under fire.” He says additional members have been deployed to the area.